The paper deals with volume estimates of metric balls in manifolds, which have applications in information and coding theory. The paper specifically focuses on the unitary group and derives new results using tools from random matrix theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). Other likely sub-categories include cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.SD (Systems and Control), cs.DS (Dynamical Systems), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
